Abdomen:
Abdominal terga excluding tergite II and outer-laterotergites uniformly and densely covered with pale elongate-ovate punctures on contrastingly black tergum (
Fig. 7
), punctures hirsute each with a long bristle. Abdominal sterna also very finely and densely punctate all over similar to terga (
Fig. 5
).

Female genitalia:
Both terga and sterna mostly as in male. Sternite VII in female not bilobed in middle. Ovipositor as in 
Figs. 11, 12
; first ramus traversing to about 2/3 length of elongate and apically pointed first gonapophysis (
Fig. 11
); second gonapophysis bladelike, slightly broadly spatulate in apical ¼ area (
Fig. 12
). Spermatheca (
Fig. 13
) lightly sclerotized, bulb spherical, no distinct flange; duct of moderate length, basal part broad and saccoid, apical part (i.e., part below apical bulb) thin and tubular (
Fig. 13
).
